  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div xml:id="Aink13-kilavi">
        <p type="edition">vāyilāyp pukkārkkut talaimakaḷ, ‘avaṉ peṇṭir naḷḷeṉ yāmattum tuyilār; avar
          aṟiyāmal avaṉ varuntiram yātu?’ eṉac colli vāyil maṟuttatu.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en"> </p>
      </div>

      <div xml:id="Aink13">
        <lg type="edition">
          <l> pariyuṭai naṉmāṉ poṅkuḷai yaṉṉa</l>
          <l> vaṭaikarai vēḻam veṇpūp pakarun</l>
          <l> taṇṭuṟai yūraṉ peṇṭir</l>
          <l> tuñcūr yāmattun tuyilaṟi yalarē.</l>
        </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
          <l> The women of the man from the village by the cool ghat–</l>
          <l rend="indent2"> where they announce the white flower of wild cane from the settling
            shore</l>
          <l rend="indent2"> that resembles the foaming manes of well-paced gold horses–</l>
          <l> won’t know sleep–even at midnight, when the village sleeps.</l>


        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
  </text>
  
